      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/qoi-relevance-level2",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index (RH) is the primary regulatory QoI for CPB device submissions per FDA guidance. Secondary QoIs include shear stress distribution and exposure time, which collectively characterize hemolysis mechanisms. Clinical relevance of RH < 1 acceptance criterion established through predicate device comparison methodology documented in FDA guidance document."
    },
